Make sure the location is dry. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d1/Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/d/d1/Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/aid3499957-v4-728px-Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Make sure the wood you want to burn is dry as well. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/cf/Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/c/cf/Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/aid3499957-v4-728px-Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

At this point, the fire should be burning pretty well. Watch out for the heat when moving around pieces. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/3/3b/Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/aid3499957-v4-728px-Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Keep adding newspaper to the pit and/or very small amounts of lighter fluid to the wood. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/2/29/Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/2/29/Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/aid3499957-v4-728px-Make-a-Bonfire-with-Lighter-Fluid-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
